WLC_GET_BACKEND_TYPE(3)                                  WLC CORE API FUNCTIONS

NAME

    wlc_get_backend_type - query which backend wlc is using

SYNOPSIS

    enum wlc_backend_type wlc_get_backend_type(void);

DESCRIPTION
    
    wlc_get_backend_type() can be used to determine which backend the
    compositor is currently running on.  This is useful if the compositor needs
    to know whether it is running nested inside an X11 (Xorg) server or
    directly on DRM for example.

RETURN VALUE

    wlc_get_backend_type() returns a wlc_backend_type which can be one of
    WLC_BACKEND_X11, WLC_BACKEND_DRM or WLC_BACKEND_NONE.

NOTES

    WLC_BACKEND_NONE shall be returned if wlc_init(3) failed or when
    wlc_get_backend_type() is called before wlc_init(3).

EXAMPLE

    #include <wlc/wlc.h>

    const enum wlc_backend_type backend = wlc_get_backend_type();

    switch (backend) {
        WLC_BACKEND_X11:
            set_default_prefix(WLC_BIT_MOD_ALT);
            break;

        default:
            set_default_prefix(WLC_BIT_MOD_LOGO);
    }
